  "texts": [
    "The models were trained using a standard 8:1:1 train-validation-test split, and the performance of each model was evaluated based on precision, recall, and F1-score.",
    "A grid search was also conducted to optimize hyperparameters for each model.",
    "The results of the study show that RoBERTa achieved the highest average F1 score of 0.8580, outperforming other models in precision and recall for identifying key entities related to construction risks.",
    "The BERT model also performed well, particularly in terms of recall, while ELECTRA showed a consistent balance between precision and recall across different risk categories.",
    "The T5 model exhibited high precision but had a low recall rate, making it less suitable for the task of identifying risk-related entities comprehensively."
  ],
